request.description:
This API endpoint allows the client to create a new player with the specified UserID. Upon a successful execution of the request, the response will include the Pid (Player ID) associated with the newly created player.

The request should be sent as an HTTP POST to {{CLIENT API ENDPOINT}}/api/v1/player/create with the UserID parameter in the query string.

The response will have a status code of 200 and a content type of application/json. The response body will contain a JSON object with the keys "code", "error", and "data". The "data" object will include the Pid (Player ID) associated with the newly created player.

Example response:

``` json
{
    "code": 0,
    "error": "",
    "data": {
        "Pid": 12345
    }
}

 ```

This endpoint makes an HTTP POST request to create a new player with the provided UserID.

#### Request Parameters

- UserID (query parameter) - The unique identifier for the user.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and has the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "code": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "error": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "Pid": {
          "type": "number"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response contains the following fields:

- code (number) - Indicates the status of the request.

- error (string) - Provides any error message, if applicable.

- data (object) - Contains the player information.

    - Pid (number) - The unique identifier for the newly created player.
